        <p>Today, Hrefna is disabled and has been for the past 10 years. "It teaches you to be yourself and you get to know yourself in a new way. You learn not to always be around everyone or in everything. The worst thing is probably the stigma that disabled people face, and the Icelanders are worse off than the Danes. They are more open to diversity than in Iceland, where the attitude is that you don't want to work or are cheating the system. As if it's desirable not to be able to work and you don't do it for the election."</p>
